-- PRESS DIGEST - RUSSIA - May 29
-- 
-- Thu May 29, 2014 04:57AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, May 29 (Reuters) - The following are some of the leading stories in Russia's newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

VEDOMOSTI www.vedomosti.ru - Russia's Economy Ministry has prepared a draft law that simplifies the process by which Russian authorities can use land in Crimea for infrastructure developments for a planned special economic zone, the daily says. - Several thousand opposition members in Georgia's breakaway region of Abkhazia held a rally on Tuesday protesting against corruption and demanding reforms, the daily reports.  KOMMERSANT www.kommersant.ru - Some 42 percent of Russians believe Russia needs to strive to become a superpower in the XXI century, the paper writes citing a recent poll by a state-run pollster VTsIOM. - Moscow authorities plan to tackle the city's traffic issues by investing around 1.05 billion roubles ($30 million) in bike rental schemes together with Sberbank <SBER.MM> and Bank of Moscow, the paper writes. - Spanish fashion chain Mango plans to open 30 shops in Russia by the end of 2014, the paper says.